1"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-cHMHbD bwTmDt pf-33_">The significance of attachment in early childhood development</span></h2><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/The_significance_of_attachment_in_early_childhood_development_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.png?v=1691570326" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/The_significance_of_attachment_in_early_childhood_development_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.png?v=1691570326 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/The_significance_of_attachment_in_early_childhood_development_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK_500x.png?v=1691570326 320w" width="1667" height="1111" alt="The significance of attachment in early childhood development - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" title="The significance of attachment in early childhood development - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-gtJxSR jkHSry pf-34_"/><p class="sc-eONOlN cfGtgs pf-35_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-cHMHbD bwTmDt pf-37_">Attachment theory explores the emotional bond between children and their significant caregivers. It revolves around the concept of attachment, which refers to the strong desire for regular contact with someone, leading to distress when separated from that person.<br><br>In the early years, secure attachments with caregivers provide a safe base for children to explore the world and develop self-confidence.</span></p><h3 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-fUklNj thmnJ pf-38_ _Y6RW61"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-cHMHbD bwTmDt pf-40_">Key concepts and theories of attachment in the early years</span></h3><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Key_concepts_and_theories_of_attachment_in_the_early_years_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.png?v=1691570397" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Key_concepts_and_theories_of_attachment_in_the_early_years_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Grou